a judge refused to spare james brown from jail 
and denied a change of venue request from his lawyer as the soul 
singers trial on assault charges began tuesday 
there will be no change of venue not one solitary soul said 
they could not give the defendant a fair trial circuit judge 
hubert e long said after the jury was selected 
browns attorney bill weeks had argued that heavy media 
coverage of the case would make it difficult for his client to 
receive a fair trial but the judge refused his request after 
questioning the 12 jurors 
the 60yearold singer was arrested sept 24 after a chase 
through augusta ga and north augusta sc he is charged with 
attempting to run over two north augusta public safety officers and 
failing to stop for a blue light and siren 
the halfhour chase ended after police shot out the tires on 
browns pickup truck it was one of several scrapes with the law the 
singer has had in the past year 
brown asked long that he be allowed to go home tuesday but the 
judge said state law requires him to be jailed during the course of 
the trial 
i volunteered to go to vietnam to sing brown said i was 
not armed i ask that you trust me let me go home and come back 
but the judge cited a law requiring a defendants bond to be 
revoked during a trial adding its nothing personal but i have 
a job to do 
browns wife adrienne who has twice claimed earlier this year 
that her husband beat her sat in the audience through the day 
