<TEXT>
rescue workers in soviet armenia like those 
in mexico city three years ago are racing against time and the 
elements to remove tons of rubble without killing people trapped 
below 
using sound equipment dogs hammers and chisels rescue crews 
searched desperately for survivors for nearly three weeks after the 
september 1985 earthquakes in mexico city 
after the first week few were found alive and they were mostly 
babies but the infants gave hope to a shattered city 
fighting infected wounds without water or food they held out in 
the tangled mass of concrete slabs reinforcing rods and crushed 
furniture of the hospitals where they were born 
one baby who was found on the ninth day after the sept 19 
quake is believed to be the last person rescued alive 
five days after the quake amid fears that demolition of 
seriously damaged buildings would begin thenpresident miguel de la 
madrid assured the country rescuers would go slowly 
we have to work with prudence so as not to put at risk the 
volunteers so the rescue work will not provoke internal caveins 
that might cost the lives of those we might still be able to find 
alive he said 
the government acknowledged 6000 deaths but estimates based on 
reports from foreign rescue crews and private mexican sources put 
the toll as high as 30000 
hundreds and perhaps thousands of people were trapped alive after 
the quake and a strong aftershock the next day that compacted the 
rubble even more 
trained dogs sniffed for signs of life or death then rescuers 
demanding silence from waiting relatives and reporters probed with 
sensitive microphones trying to home in on sounds and determine a 
victims exact location 
rescuers tunneled in with everything from drills to jackhammers 
blow torches shovels and saws 
mexico citys mild climate worked in favor of those trapped with 
temperatures in the 70s during the day and the 50s at night 
although downpours are common in september it stayed dry in the 
days after the quakes 
for many victims in this city of 18 million help came too late 
anyway for some miracles unfolded 
at what was the 12story juarez hospital near the bottom of a 
