a subsidiary of gannett co inc and two other 
outdoor advertising firms conspired to fix prices for southern 
california billboard space a federal grand jury has charged 
a spokeswoman for gannett which runs north americas largest 
outdoor advertising company said the charges were baseless and 
would be contested vigorously 
the monopoly was run by gannett outdoor of southern california 
and former chairman and chief executive officer hal brown 
metromedia inc of secaucus nj and former vice president michael 
f tobey and foster and kleiser corp of delaware said judy 
whalley of the us justice department in washington 
