<TEXT>
much of the east today remained in the icy grip of arctic air 
that brought record low temperatures while chinook winds howled 
through the rockies 
temperatures dropped below zero in eastern new york state and 
northern new england but the cold was less intense and widespread 
than during sunday night and monday morning 
albany ny set a record for todays date when the mercury 
plunged to 5 below zero breaking the 1960 record of minus 1 
shortly before midnight baltimore tied its record for dec 12 at 10 
degrees and newark nj broke its 1960 record of 9 with a 6degree 
reading 
the nations high temperature monday was 88 degrees at san 
gabriel calif 
light snow fell ahead of a cold front moving through the great 
lakes region up to 3 inches covered several areas in wisconsin and 
northern illinois received an inch or less 
the snow spread eastward into northeast indiana ohio and parts 
of kentucky and michigan strong gusty winds accompanied the snow 
reducing visibilities the snow was expected to move into western 
pennsylvania this morning 
a developing area of low pressure off floridas east coast 
produced sleet and snow along coastal areas of north carolina 
windy conditions developed in the northern rockies ahead of a 
cold front moving across the pacific northwest livingston mont 
recorded a gust of 58 mph monday evening a high wind warning 
remained in effect this morning for the east slopes of the rockies 
and the upper yellowstone valley in montana 
the chinooks or winds that blow down the eastern slopes of the 
rockies were expected to spread southward into the central rockies 
today 
the cold front over the pacific northwest produced rain along the 
northern pacific coast and snow in the cascade mountains a snow 
advisory was in effect today for the cascades of washington state 
