<DOCNO> AP881213-0049 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
iran received the final delivery of 50 
fighter jets from china before the aug 20 ceasefire in its war 
with iraq wellinformed diplomatic sources reported today 
the j6 and f7 jets chinese versions of the sovietbuilt mig19 
and mig21 were delivered by ship over three years in knockeddown 
form through irans persian gulf port of bandar abbas a key naval 
and air base and assembled in iran the sources said 
the sources speaking on condition of anonymity said the chinese 
jets along with a large quantity of airtoair missiles were 
allocated to the revolutionary guards air wing not the regular air 
force 
western military officials could not confirm the delivery but 
don kerr an aviation specialist with the londonbased international 
institute for strategic studies said the jets had been expected 
for some time 
the quantity and the timing are certainly right for the 
iranians in their effort to develop weapons systems from other 
sources to get around their very serious problems of supply for 
their usbuilt equipment kerr said in a telephone interview 
china is irans major arms supplier and has provided ayatollah 
ruhollah khomeinis regime with antiship silkworm missiles and a 
squadron of 10 j6s in 1985 for training purposes 
irans military collapsed in a series of iraqi victories before 
the united nationssponsored ceasefire took effect and it is 
seeking to rebuild its forces 
the international institute for strategic studies reported last 
year that iran signed a 16 billion deal with beijing in 1985 for 
combat aircraft tanks and artillery 
mednews a parisbased newsletter specializing in middle east 
defense issues reported nov 21 that the deal involved what it 
identified as 60 f7 and f7m jets each costing more than 6 
million between july 1985 and february 1987 
however the diplomatic sources reported that final deliveries 
were delayed until earlier this year 
mednews quoting what it said was a copy of the contract between 
the chinese and the iranians said beijing also agreed to supply 500 
pl2 and 2000 pl2a airtoairmissiles modeled on the us 
sidewinder missile 
also in the deal were 1000 pl7 airtoair missiles copied from 
the french r550 matra weapon and 72500 57mm airtoground 
rockets mednews said 
the chinese also contracted to provide spare engines and 
technical backup with aircrews and ground crews to train iranians 
mednews reported 
china has denied it sells arms to iran or iraq although the 
institute for strategic studies lists j6 fighters in iraqs air 
force inventory 
the delivery of the jets virtually doubled the size of irans 
badly depleted air strength but none of the chinese fighters was 
ever reported in combat even when the iranians were suffering 
military defeats between april and july 
it takes three years to get personnel trained and operational 
on new aircraft kerr said so its not surprising the f7s were 
not committed in the fighting earlier this year even when the 
iranians had their backs to the wall 
the personnel flying these planes would still have been very 
inexperienced 
the iranian air force was built around ussupplied f4 
phantoms f5 tigers and f14 tomcats delivered before khomeinis 
