president reagan looking back on his eight 
years in the white house said tuesday that one of his great 
disappointments is leaving office without taming the federal 
budget deficit 
reagan had come into office promising to balance the nations 
redink spending by 1984 
the president who leaves office in less than six weeks 
contended that a washington colony composed of an iron 
triangle of members of congress the news media and special 
interest groups had helped perpetuate the deficit 
when i came to office i found the presidency a weakened 
institution reagan told his audience of several hundred 
government officials and employees at constitution hall 
i found a congress that was trying to transform our government 
