spending bills 
reagan received a tumultuous reception with applause punctuated 
by cheers and whistles from his audiences of government officials 
and employees in constitution hall 
one of my great disappointments as i leave office is that the 
federal budget itself is not yet balanced the president said 
the house of representatives he said has become a virtually 
permament chamber no longer truly responsive to the people 
with a 98 percent rate of reelection there is less turnover 
in the house than in the supreme soviet he said 
the president said the iron triangle also derives from the 
