a widow has beaten the louvre and its army of 
highpowered art experts in a 20year legal battle over ownership of 
a 17th century painting that she has sold for 14 million 
the louvre bought olympos and marsyas the rustic scene by 
17th century landscape artist nicolas poussin for 366 in 1968 
but owner suzanne saintarroman 78 won her fight in the french 
courts and forced the gallery to take it out of storage and return 
it to her 
